  "response": "The word 'dexterous' is an adjective that describes someone who is skillful, especially with their hands, or who is mentally agile and clever. Here are a few examples of how it can be used in a sentence:\n\n1. **Physical Skill**:  \n   - \"The dexterous magician amazed the audience with his ability to manipulate cards effortlessly.\"  \n   - \"She was so dexterous with the sewing needle that she could mend a tear in minutes.\"\n\n2. **Mental Agility**:  \n   - \"His dexterous mind allowed him to solve complex problems with ease.\"  \n   - \"The politician was dexterous in navigating the tricky questions during the debate.\"\n\n3. **Versatility**:  \n   - \"As a dexterous artist, she excelled in both painting and sculpting.\"  \n\nIn each case, 'dexterous' highlights a person's skill, adeptness, or quick thinking.",
